    <mypublications>
      <h2>Projects: Computer Vision</h2>
      <p>
      <hr>
      
      <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><img src="docs/images/boundarydet.png" width= "25%" vspace="5%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>Features on Object Boundaries
<date>(Dec 2012 - Present)</date>
</h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"> <ul>
<li>Traditional gradient-based features fail at depth discontinuities due to object motion against a varying background. Our features work on the curve describing the object leading to more accurate tracking.
</li>
</ul>
</p>
        <p class = "publicationsummary"><a href="http://arxiv.org/
abs/1412.1957"> CoMIC: Corners on Maximally-stable Iso-intenstiy Curves</a>,
Swarna Kamlam Ravindran and Anurag Mittal, under review at IEEE CVPR 2015  <a href =" https://swarnakr.github.io/">supplementary material</a>.
        <p class = "publicationsummary">CoMIC features for Tracking and Image Matching, Swarna Kamlam Ravindran and Anurag Mittal, IJCV draft in preparation.
</p>

</p>

<!----------------------------------------->
  
      </div>
      <hr>
      
      <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><a href="#"><img src="docs/images/iitmLogo.png" width="19%" hspace="5%" vspace="7%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>Features for Panoroma Applications
<date>(Dec 2009 - Dec 2010)</date>
</h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"><ul><li> A feature detector using a probabilistic combination of stable extremal regions
incorporated into a 3D reconstruction system.

</li><li>Mosaicing and Contour detection software were implemented by using shape
geometry to achieve scale invariance.</li>
</ul>
</p>

      </div>
      <hr>
<!----------------------------------------->
  
      
      <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><a href="#"><img src="docs/images/face.png" width="25%" vspace="2%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>3D Face Recognition <date>(Dec 2008 - May 2009)</date>
</h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"><ul><li> Designed a face recognition system using a descriptor formed as a 2D histogram of distances between points near a landmark point to the corresponding tangent plane. Experiments were performed on range images of six subjects with varying illumination. 
</li></ul>
</p>
        <p class = "publicationsummary"><h7>3D Face Recognition system using a Local Shape Descriptor</h7>, Swarna Kamlam Ravindran and Sumithra G, International Symposium on Computing, Communication, and Control (ISCCC) 2009.
</p>
      </div>
<hr>
<!----------------------------------------->
        
      <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><a href="#"><img src="docs/images/bag.png" width="20%" hspace="2%" vspace="1%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>Bag detection for TCS project <date>(Jul 2008 - Dec 2008)</date></h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"><ul><li> Principles of symmetricity were used to identify humans carrying bags or other
objects. Periodocity check was employed to identify vehicles or animals in motion.
</li></ul>
</p>
     </div>
      <hr>

<!----------------------------------------->
  
             <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><a href="#"><img src="docs/images/pr.png" width="25%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>Modules for Music & Speech projects, IIT
<date>(Nov 2011 - Feb 2012)</date></h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"><ul><li>Data classification was performed using Linde Buzo Algorithm and K means clustering.
	</li><li>Bayesian Clustering and Bayesian classification using BE, ML, MAP was implemented to classify high-dimensional data points.
</li></ul>
	</p>
       <p class = "fig">
	<figure><a href="docs/PatternRecog.zip"><img src="docs/images/code.png" width="5%" alt="" hspace = "40%" align="left"/></a></figure>          	</p>
      </div>
<hr>

<!----------------------------------------->

      <div id="rpublication">
        <figure><a href="#"><img src="docs/images/cv.png" width="32%" style="PADDING-TOP: 5%" alt="" align="left"/></a></figure>    
        <h3>Projects in Computer Vision <date>(May 2011 - Jul 2011)</date></h3>
        <p class = "publicationbib"><ul><li>Codes for Image Mosaicing, Image Rectification and Parabola detection using Hough transform were developed</li></ul>
	</p>
       <p class = "fig">
	<figure><a href="docs/cv_projects.zip"><img src="docs/images/code.png" width="5%" alt="" hspace = "40%" align="left"/></a></figure>          	</p>
      </div>
